_sText:
Take a ride through the tunnel of love.

This map is my submission for the KSF Spring Mapping Contest 2020 in which the theme for the competition was 'sunnyhappylove'. My take on the theme was that of a romantic tunnel of love style ride through several unique environments, ending in a warm, summery beach area. This map is tier 1, with several skips, allowing surfers of all skill levels to enjoy and have fun with the map. A big thanks to everyone at KSF involved in organising and executing this competition, as well as everyone who contributed to the already generous prize pool. Your support for the mapping community is greatly appreciated :)

D- Pickles hand crafted this map back in April of 2015 after meticulously studying the source engine code for over 12 years. He somehow gained access to the source engine a year before it was released to the general public. My suspicions is that he is an ex-valve employee. 

Pickles' final words to the TF2 community before releasing this map were as follows: Welcome to surf_kaboom! After 12 years in development, hopefully it will have been worth the wait.

When I was porting it, my computer couldn't handle the stress of such a powerful and beautifully detailed map that I had a few blue screens during the process. I really felt like I was tampering with God's work here. Legend has it Pickles created this masterpiece only using the carve tool. 

Download at your own risk.

= Surf_Ivory by Sid =

Some of the most popular maps in the surfing world are very visually appealling, and in most cases, not very difficult to complete, which draws in a lot of players. Realizing this, I set out to create a new surf map, and now present to you; Surf_Ivory!

This map is set in a large, open landscape featuring lush green gardens and elegant stone. The surf is very fast, very large and intuitive to navigate. While being designed with novice players in mind, more skilled players will enjoy finding shortcuts and the perfect line!

- Tier 2 Linear, roughly a minute in length
- 3 bonus stages (Created by draph, donkey and not_a_zombie!)

!IMPORTANT! This map requires the max velocity to be set to 5000!

surf_hourglass - a tier 1 map meant for both first timers as well as veteran surfers with a well thought out fast route. The map alternates the player between two timelines, and it includes a lot of rarely seen features in Source Engine maps, like moving clouds, dynamically changing skybox, color correction and expensive water on more than one Z axis at once. The map was made for a KSF mapping contest, where it has not won any prizes, but got an honorable mention. As a note from me, I started working on the map around 3 weeks before the contest's deadline, so I unfortunately did not have the time to polish the map and it feels unfinished to me, but I had no other choice than to release it - I hope you enjoy playing it anyway :)

FOR SERVER OWNERS:
- designed for 66/64 tickrate, 150 sv_airaccelerate, 5000 sv_maxvelocity
- in order for all of the map features to work properly, do NOT remove any entities using plugins like stripper etc. on your server

FOR PLAYERS:
- client-side, make sure HDR and color correction are enabled and mat_specular is 1
- if the map appears too dark in some parts, I recommend raising the brightness settings, and if that doesn't help, in worst case you can also disable HDR which will make the map way brighter (but also uglier)

Made for the 2020 KSF Spring Skill Surf Mapping Contest

The theme is around green candy forest with chocolate rivers 
The given theme keywords were "sunnyhappylove",  and I went with a sunny cliffy forest environment where sweets are found in nature itself.

The surf is symmetrical in the beginning and then joins back again in one route until the end. The map is about 50 secs long +- 10 secs depending on speed. There are also a few ramps you can skip, for higher speed surfers.

So yeah. I had quite a alot of fun making this map, and the custom stuff and all, and I hope people do too playing it )

Tier 3 - 4 linear surf map. + 1 bonus stage

The theme of this map is a floating greenhouse complex in the sky. Includes soundscapes for those who prefer to surf with their sound on. The surf is a compact style with a mix of 2-way and 4-way symmetry on the main map. The bonus is fully comprised of 8 way symmetry.

Special thanks to Draph for creating the credits and main title board texture in spawn. Thank you to Chrissybear + wife for motivating me to map and helping me settle with a name. Thank you to Bocuma for showcasing this map (in a slightly earlier development state).

This map was made for the Spring 2020 KSF Surf Mapping Contest.

The theme given was "sunnyhappylove" so for my map I decided to go with what I and hopefully others love in surf. I went and got inspiration from one of my favourite surf maps of all time; surf_mushroom(_ksf). My goal was to capture the same style of surf of mushroom without all the gimmicky stuff it has. Also I added in alot of nature elements for the cozy feel. What isn't more happylove about someone so inspired by a map he wants to make it into his own style just so he can enjoy it in some way even more :).

The map is somewhere between 45 seconds and 1 minute.
